article.headline: Bjorklund puts up 17, St. Thomas beats Denver 83-58
article.description: — Parker Bjorklund's 17 points helped St. Thomas defeat Denver 83-58 on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Bjorklund puts up 17, St. Thomas beats Denver 83-58
article.story: ST. PAUL, Minn. -- — Parker Bjorklund's 17 points helped St. Thomas defeat Denver 83-58 on Saturday night. Bjorklund also had seven rebounds for the Tommies (19-12, 9-7 Summit League). Kendall Blue scored 13 points and added seven rebounds. Raheem Anthony shot 5 for 10, including 2 for 4 from beyond the arc to finish with 12 points, while adding five rebounds and six assists. DeAndre Craig finished with 11 points for the Pioneers (15-16, 6-10). Tyson Garff added 11 points for Denver. In addition, Pedro Lopez-Sanvicente had 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
